.TH "drm_property_create_signed_range" 9 "drm_property_create_signed_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_property_create_signed_range \- create a new signed ranged property type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_property *" drm_property_create_signed_range
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "int64_t min "  ","
.BI "int64_t max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
drm device
.IP "flags" 12
flags specifying the property type
.IP "name" 12
name of the property
.IP "min" 12
minimum value of the property
.IP "max" 12
maximum value of the property
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This creates a new generic drm property which can then be attached to a drm
object with \fBdrm_object_attach_property\fP. The returned property object must
be freed with \fBdrm_property_destroy\fP, which is done automatically when
calling \fBdrm_mode_config_cleanup\fP.

Userspace is allowed to set any signed integer value in the (min, max)
range inclusive.
.SH "RETURN"
A pointer to the newly created property on success, NULL on failure.
